  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Gospel Exalted'
      title: The Gospel Exalted
      number: 1
      content: '  Paul, a bond-servant of Christ Jesus, called as an apostle (special
        messenger, personally chosen representative), set apart for [preaching] the
        gospel of God [the good news of salvation], '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "which He promised beforehand through His prophets in the sacred Scriptures\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '[the good news] regarding His Son, who, as to the flesh [His human
        nature], was born a descendant of David [to fulfill the covenant promises], '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and [as to His divine nature] according to the Spirit of holiness
        was openly designated to be the Son of God with power [in a triumphant and
        miraculous way] by His resurrection from the dead: Jesus Christ our Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It is through Him that we have received grace and [our] apostleship
        to promote obedience to the faith and make disciples for His name\u2019s
        sake among all the Gentiles, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and you also are among those who are called of Jesus Christ to belong
        to Him;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "[I am writing] to all who are beloved of God in Rome, called to be
        saints (God\u2019s people) and set apart for a sanctified life, [that is,
        set apart for God and His purpose]: Grace to you and peace [inner calm and
        spiritual well-being] from God our Father and from the Lord Jesus Christ.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for all of you, because
        your faith [your trust and confidence in His power, wisdom, and goodness]
        is being proclaimed in all the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For God, whom I serve with my spirit by preaching the gospel of His
        Son, is my witness as to how continuously I mention you '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "in my prayers; always pleading that somehow, by God\u2019s will,
        I may now at last come to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For I long to see you so that I may share with you some spiritual
        gift, to strengthen and establish you; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "that is, that we may be mutually encouraged and comforted by each
        other\u2019s faith, both yours and mine. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I do not want you to be unaware, brothers and sisters, that many
        times I have planned to come to you, (and have been prevented so far) so
        that I may have some fruit [of my labors] among you, even as I have among
        the rest of the Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have a duty to perform and a debt to pay both to Greeks and to
        barbarians [the cultured and the uncultured], both to the wise and to the
        foolish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So, for my part, I am ready and eager to preach the gospel also to
        you who are in Rome.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I am not ashamed of the gospel, for it is the power of God for salvation
        [from His wrath and punishment] to everyone who believes [in Christ as Savior],
        to the Jew first and also to the Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Unbelief and Its Consequences'
      title: Unbelief and Its Consequences
      number: 17
      content: "For in the gospel the righteousness of God is revealed, both springing
        from faith and leading to faith [disclosed in a way that awakens more faith].
        As it is written and forever remains written, \u201CThe just  and  upright
        shall live by faith.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For [God does not overlook sin and] the wrath of God is revealed
        from heaven against all ungodliness and unrighteousness of men who in their
        wickedness suppress and stifle the truth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'because that which is known about God is evident within them [in
        their inner consciousness], for God made it evident to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For ever since the creation of the world His invisible attributes,
        His eternal power and divine nature, have been clearly seen, being understood
        through His workmanship [all His creation, the wonderful things that He has
        made], so that they [who fail to believe and trust in Him] are without excuse
        and without defense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For even though they knew God [as the Creator], they did not honor
        Him as God or give thanks [for His wondrous creation]. On the contrary, they
        became worthless in their thinking [godless, with pointless reasonings, and
        silly speculations], and their foolish heart was darkened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Claiming to be wise, they became fools, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and exchanged the glory and majesty and excellence of the immortal
        God for an image [worthless idols] in the shape of mortal man and birds and
        four-footed animals and reptiles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Therefore God gave them over in the lusts of their own hearts to
        [sexual] impurity, so that their bodies would be dishonored among them [abandoning
        them to the degrading power of sin], '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'because [by choice] they exchanged the truth of God for a lie, and
        worshiped and served the creature rather than the Creator, who is blessed
        forever! Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For this reason God gave them over to degrading and vile passions;
        for their women exchanged the natural function for that which is unnatural
        [a function contrary to nature], '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and in the same way also the men turned away from the natural function
        of the woman and were consumed with their desire toward one another, men
        with men committing shameful acts and in return receiving in their own bodies
        the inevitable and appropriate penalty for their wrongdoing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And since they did not see fit to acknowledge God or consider Him
        worth knowing [as their Creator], God gave them over to a depraved mind,
        to do things which are improper and repulsive, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'until they were filled (permeated, saturated) with every kind of
        unrighteousness, wickedness, greed, evil; full of envy, murder, strife, deceit,
        malice and mean-spiritedness. They are gossips [spreading rumors], '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'slanderers, haters of God, insolent, arrogant, boastful, inventors
        [of new forms] of evil, disobedient and disrespectful to parents, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'without understanding, untrustworthy, unloving, unmerciful [without
        pity]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Although they know God\u2019s righteous decree and His judgment,
        that those who do such things deserve death, yet they not only do them, but
        they even [enthusiastically] approve and tolerate others who practice them."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Impartiality of God'
      title: The Impartiality of God
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore you have no excuse or justification, everyone of you
        who [hypocritically] judges and condemns others; for in passing judgment
        on another person, you condemn yourself, because you who judge [from a position
        of arrogance or self-righteousness] are habitually practicing the very same
        things [which you denounce]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And we know that the judgment of God falls justly and in accordance
        with truth on those who practice such things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But do you think this, O man, when you judge and condemn those who
        practice such things, and yet do the same yourself, that you will escape
        God\u2019s judgment and elude His verdict? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Or do you have no regard for the wealth of His kindness and tolerance
        and patience [in withholding His wrath]? Are you [actually] unaware or ignorant
        [of the fact] that God\u2019s kindness leads you to repentance [that is,
        to change your inner self, your old way of thinking\u2014seek His purpose
        for your life]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But because of your callous stubbornness and unrepentant heart you
        are [deliberately] storing up wrath for yourself on the day of wrath when
        God\u2019s righteous judgment will be revealed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He will pay back to each person according to his deeds [justly, as
        his deeds deserve]: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'to those who by persistence in doing good seek [unseen but certain
        heavenly] glory, honor, and immortality, [He will give the gift of] eternal
        life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But for those who are selfishly ambitious and self-seeking and disobedient
        to the truth but responsive to wickedness, [there will be] wrath and indignation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'There will be tribulation and anguish [torturing confinement] for
        every human soul who does [or permits] evil, to the Jew first and also to
        the Greek, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but glory and honor and inner peace [will be given] to everyone who
        habitually does good, to the Jew first and also to the Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For God shows no partiality [no arbitrary favoritism; with Him one
        person is not more important than another].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For all who have sinned without the Law will also perish without
        [regard to] the Law, and all who have sinned under the Law will be judged
        and condemned by the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For it is not those who merely hear the Law [as it is read aloud]
        who are just or righteous before God, but it is those who [actually] obey
        the Law who will be justified [pronounced free of the guilt of sin and declared
        acceptable to Him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When Gentiles, who do not have the Law [since it was given only to
        Jews], do instinctively the things the Law requires [guided only by their
        conscience], they are a law to themselves, though they do not have the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They show that the essential requirements of the Law are written
        in their hearts; and their conscience [their sense of right and wrong, their
        moral choices] bearing witness and their thoughts alternately accusing or
        perhaps defending them '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Jew Is Condemned by the Law'
      title: The Jew Is Condemned by the Law
      number: 16
      content: 'on that day when, as my gospel proclaims, God will judge the secrets
        [all the hidden thoughts and concealed sins] of men through Christ Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But if you bear the name \u201CJew\u201D and rely on the Law [for
        your salvation] and boast in [your special relationship to] God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and [if you claim to] know His will and approve the things that are
        essential or have a sense of what is excellent, based on your instruction
        from the Law, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and [if you] are confident that you are a [qualified] guide to the
        blind [those untaught in theology], a light to those who are in darkness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and [that you are] a corrector of the foolish, a teacher of the [spiritually]
        childish, having in the Law the embodiment of knowledge and of the truth\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'well then, you who teach others, do you not teach yourself? You who
        preach against stealing, do you steal [in ways that are discrete, but just
        as sinful]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You who say that one must not commit adultery, do you commit adultery?
        You who detest idols, do you rob [pagan] temples [of valuable idols and offerings]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You who boast in the Law, do you [repeatedly] dishonor God by breaking
        the Law? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "For, \u201Cthe name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles because
        of you,\u201D just as it is written [in Scripture].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Circumcision [the sign of the covenant of Abraham] is indeed of value
        if you practice the Law; but if you habitually break the Law, your circumcision
        has become uncircumcision [it is meaningless in God\u2019s sight]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So if the uncircumcised man keeps the requirements of the Law, will
        not his uncircumcision be regarded [by God] as circumcision? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then he who is physically uncircumcised but keeps [the spirit of]
        the Law will judge you who, even though you have the written code and circumcision,
        break the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For he is not a [real] Jew who is only one outwardly, nor is [true]
        circumcision something external and physical. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: But he is a Jew who is one inwardly; and [true] circumcision is circumcision
        of the heart, by the Spirit, not by [the fulfillment of] the letter [of the
        Law]. His praise is not from men, but from God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: All the World Guilty'
      title: All the World Guilty
      number: 1
      content: '  Then what is the advantage of the Jew? Or what is the benefit of
        circumcision? '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Great in every respect. To begin with, the Jews were entrusted with
        the oracles of God [His very words]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'What then? If some did not believe or were unfaithful [to God], their
        lack of belief will not nullify and make invalid the faithfulness of God
        and His word, will it? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Certainly not! Let God be found true [as He will be], though every
        person be found a liar, just as it is written [in Scripture],\u201CThat You
        may be justified in Your words,And prevail when You are judged [by sinful
        men].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But if our unrighteousness demonstrates the righteousness of God,
        what shall we say? God is not wrong to inflict His wrath [on us], is He?
        (I am speaking in purely human terms.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Certainly not! For otherwise, how will God judge the world? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But [as you might say] if through my lie God\u2019s truth was magnified
        and abounded to His glory, why am I still being judged as a sinner? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And why not say, (as some slanderously report and claim that we teach)
        \u201CLet us do evil so that good may come of it\u201D? Their condemnation
        [by God] is just.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Well then, are we [Jews] better off than they? Not at all; for we
        have already charged that both Jews and Greeks (Gentiles) are under the control
        of sin and subject to its power. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As it is written and forever remains written,\u201CThere is none
        righteous [none that meets God\u2019s standard], not even one.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'There is none who understands,There is none who seeks for God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "All have turned aside, together they have become useless;There is
        none who does good, no, not one.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CTheir throat is an open grave;They [habitually] deceive with
        their tongues.\u201D\u201CThe venom of asps is beneath their lips.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTheir mouth is full of cursing and bitterness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CTheir feet are swift to shed blood,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Destruction and misery are in their paths,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they have not known the path of peace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThere is no fear of God [and His awesome power] before their
        eyes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now we know that whatever the Law [of Moses] says, it speaks to those
        who are under the Law, so that [the excuses of] every mouth may be silenced
        [from protesting] and that all the world may be held accountable to God [and
        subject to His judgment]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Justification by Faith'
      title: Justification by Faith
      number: 20
      content: 'For no person will be justified [freed of guilt and declared righteous]
        in His sight by [trying to do] the works of the Law. For through the Law
        we become conscious of sin [and the recognition of sin directs us toward
        repentance, but provides no remedy for sin].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But now the righteousness of God has been clearly revealed [independently
        and completely] apart from the Law, though it is [actually] confirmed by
        the Law and the [words and writings of the] Prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "This righteousness of God comes through faith in Jesus Christ for
        all those [Jew or Gentile] who believe [and trust in Him and acknowledge
        Him as God\u2019s Son]. There is no distinction, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'since all have sinned and continually fall short of the glory of
        God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and are being justified [declared free of the guilt of sin, made
        acceptable to God, and granted eternal life] as a gift by His [precious,
        undeserved] grace, through the redemption [the payment for our sin] which
        is [provided] in Christ Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "whom God displayed publicly [before the eyes of the world] as a [life-giving]
        sacrifice of atonement and reconciliation (propitiation) by His blood [to
        be received] through faith. This was to demonstrate His righteousness [which
        demands punishment for sin], because in His forbearance [His deliberate restraint]
        He passed over the sins previously committed [before Jesus\u2019 crucifixion]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'It was to demonstrate His righteousness at the present time, so that
        He would be just and the One who justifies those who have faith in Jesus
        [and rely confidently on Him as Savior].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then what becomes of [our] boasting? It is excluded [entirely ruled
        out, banished]. On what principle? On [the principle of good] works? No,
        but on the principle of faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'For we maintain that an individual is justified by faith distinctly
        apart from works of the Law [the observance of which has nothing to do with
        justification, that is, being declared free of the guilt of sin and made
        acceptable to God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Or is God the God of Jews only? Is He not also the God of Gentiles
        [who were not given the Law]? Yes, of Gentiles also, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'since indeed it is one [and the same] God who will justify the circumcised
        by faith [which began with Abraham] and the uncircumcised through [their
        newly acquired] faith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Do we then nullify the Law by this faith [making the Law of no effect,
        overthrowing it]? Certainly not! On the contrary, we confirm and establish
        and uphold the Law [since it convicts us all of sin, pointing to the need
        for salvation].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Justification by Faith Evidenced in Old Testament'
      title: Justification by Faith Evidenced in Old Testament
      number: 1
      content: '  What then shall we say that Abraham, our forefather humanly speaking,
        has found? [Has he obtained a favored standing?] '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if Abraham was justified [that is, acquitted from the guilt of
        his sins] by works [those things he did that were good], he has something
        to boast about, but not before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For what does the Scripture say? \u201CAbraham believed in (trusted,
        relied on) God, and it was credited to his account as righteousness (right
        living, right standing with God).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now to a laborer, his wages are not credited as a favor or a gift,
        but as an obligation [something owed to him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But to the one who does not work [that is, the one who does not try
        to earn his salvation by doing good], but believes and completely trusts
        in Him who justifies the ungodly, his faith is credited to him as righteousness
        (right standing with God). '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And in this same way David speaks of the blessing on the one to whom
        God credits righteousness apart from works:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBlessed  and  happy  and  favored are those whose lawless acts
        have been forgiven,And whose sins have been covered up  and  completely buried.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Blessed  and  happy  and  favored is the man whose sin the Lord will
        not take into account  nor  charge against him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Is this blessing only for the circumcised, or also for the uncircumcised?
        For we say, \u201CFaith was credited to Abraham as righteousness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'How then was it credited [to him]? Was it after he had been circumcised,
        or before? Not after, but while [he was] uncircumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He received the sign of circumcision, a seal or confirmation of the
        righteousness which he had by faith while [he was still] uncircumcised\u2014this
        was so that he would be the [spiritual] father of all who believe without
        being circumcised\u2014so that righteousness would be credited to them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and [that he would be] the [spiritual] father of those circumcised
        who are not only circumcised, but who also walk in the steps of the faith
        of our father Abraham which he had before he was circumcised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the promise to Abraham or to his descendants that he would be
        heir of the world was not through [observing the requirements of] the Law,
        but through the righteousness of faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If those who are [followers] of the Law are [the true] heirs [of
        Abraham], then faith [leading to salvation] is of no effect and void, and
        the promise [of God] is nullified. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For the Law results in [God\u2019s] wrath [against sin], but where
        there is no law, there is no violation [of it either].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore, [inheriting] the promise depends entirely on faith [that
        is, confident trust in the unseen God], in order that it may be given as
        an act of grace [His unmerited favor and mercy], so that the promise will
        be [legally] guaranteed to all the descendants [of Abraham]\u2014not only
        for those [Jewish believers] who keep the Law, but also for those [Gentile
        believers] who share the faith of Abraham, who is the [spiritual] father
        of us all\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "(as it is written [in Scripture], \u201CI have made you a father
        of many nations\u201D) in the sight of Him in whom he believed, that is,
        God who gives life to the dead and calls into being that which does not exist. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "In hope against hope Abraham believed that he would become a father
        of many nations, as he had been promised [by God]: \u201CSo [numberless]
        shall your descendants be.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Without becoming weak in faith he considered his own body, now as
        good as dead [for producing children] since he was about a hundred years
        old, and [he considered] the deadness of Sarah\u2019s womb. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But he did not doubt or waver in unbelief concerning the promise
        of God, but he grew strong and empowered by faith, giving glory to God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'being fully convinced that God had the power to do what He had promised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Therefore his faith was credited to him as righteousness (right standing
        with God). '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now not for his sake alone was it written that it was credited to
        him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "but for our sake also\u2014to whom righteousness will be credited,
        as those who believe in Him who raised Jesus our Lord from the dead\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "who was betrayed and crucified because of our sins, and was raised
        [from the dead] because of our justification [our acquittal\u2014absolving
        us of all sin before God]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Results of Justification'
      title: Results of Justification
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, since we have been justified [that is, acquitted of
        sin, declared blameless before God] by faith, [let us grasp the fact that]
        we have peace with God [and the joy of reconciliation with Him] through our
        Lord Jesus Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Through Him we also have access by faith into this [remarkable state
        of] grace in which we [firmly and safely and securely] stand. Let us rejoice
        in our hope and the confident assurance of [experiencing and enjoying] the
        glory of [our great] God [the manifestation of His excellence and power]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And not only this, but [with joy] let us exult in our sufferings
        and rejoice in our hardships, knowing that hardship (distress, pressure,
        trouble) produces patient endurance; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and endurance, proven character (spiritual maturity); and proven
        character, hope and confident assurance [of eternal salvation]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Such hope [in God\u2019s promises] never disappoints us, because
        God\u2019s love has been abundantly poured out within our hearts through
        the Holy Spirit who was given to us.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'While we were still helpless [powerless to provide for our salvation],
        at the right time Christ died [as a substitute] for the ungodly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now it is an extraordinary thing for one to willingly give his life
        even for an upright man, though perhaps for a good man [one who is noble
        and selfless and worthy] someone might even dare to die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But God clearly shows and proves His own love for us, by the fact
        that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore, since we have now been justified [declared free of the
        guilt of sin] by His blood, [how much more certain is it that] we will be
        saved from the wrath of God through Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For if while we were enemies we were reconciled to God through the
        death of His Son, it is much more certain, having been reconciled, that we
        will be saved [from the consequences of sin] by His life [that is, we will
        be saved because Christ lives today]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Not only that, but we also rejoice in God [rejoicing in His love
        and perfection] through our Lord Jesus Christ, through whom we have now received
        and enjoy our reconciliation [with God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore, just as sin came into the world through one man, and death
        through sin, so death spread to all people [no one being able to stop it
        or escape its power], because they all sinned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Sin was [committed] in the world before the Law [was given], but
        sin is not charged [against anyone] when there is no law [against it]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Yet death ruled [over mankind] from Adam to Moses [the Lawgiver],
        even over those who had not sinned as Adam did. Adam is a type of Him (Christ)
        who was to come [but in reverse\u2014Adam brought destruction, Christ brought
        salvation].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But the free gift [of God] is not like the trespass [because the
        gift of grace overwhelms the fall of man]. For if many died by one man\u2019s
        trespass [Adam\u2019s sin], much more [abundantly] did God\u2019s grace and
        the gift [that comes] by the grace of the one Man, Jesus Christ, overflow
        to [benefit] the many. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Nor is the gift [of grace] like that which came through the one who
        sinned. For on the one hand the judgment [following the sin] resulted from
        one trespass and brought condemnation, but on the other hand the free gift
        resulted from many trespasses and brought justification [the release from
        sin\u2019s penalty for those who believe]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For if by the trespass of the one (Adam), death reigned through the
        one (Adam), much more surely will those who receive the abundance of grace
        and the free gift of righteousness reign in [eternal] life through the One,
        Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So then as through one trespass [Adam\u2019s sin] there resulted
        condemnation for all men, even so through one act of righteousness there
        resulted justification of life to all men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For just as through one man\u2019s disobedience [his failure to hear,
        his carelessness] the many were made sinners, so through the obedience of
        the one Man the many will be made righteous and acceptable to God and brought
        into right standing with Him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But the Law came to increase and expand [the awareness of] the trespass
        [by defining and unmasking sin]. But where sin increased, [God\u2019s remarkable,
        gracious gift of] grace [His unmerited favor] has surpassed it and increased
        all the more, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: so that, as sin reigned in death, so also grace would reign through
        righteousness which brings eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Believers Are Dead to Sin, Alive to God'
      title: Believers Are Dead to Sin, Alive to God
      number: 1
      content: "  What shall we say [to all this]? Should we continue in sin and
        practice sin as a habit so that [God\u2019s gift of] grace may increase and
        overflow? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Certainly not! How can we, the very ones who died to sin, continue
        to live in it any longer? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Or are you ignorant of the fact that all of us who have been baptized
        into Christ Jesus were baptized into His death? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'We have therefore been buried with Him through baptism into death,
        so that just as Christ was raised from the dead through the glory and power
        of the Father, we too might walk habitually in newness of life [abandoning
        our old ways]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For if we have become one with Him [permanently united] in the likeness
        of His death, we will also certainly be [one with Him and share fully] in
        the likeness of His resurrection. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'We know that our old self [our human nature without the Holy Spirit]
        was nailed to the cross with Him, in order that our body of sin might be
        done away with, so that we would no longer be slaves to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the person who has died [with Christ] has been freed from [the
        power of] sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now if we have died with Christ, we believe that we will also live
        [together] with Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'because we know [the self-evident truth] that Christ, having been
        raised from the dead, will never die again; death no longer has power over
        Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For the death that He died, He died to sin [ending its power and
        paying the sinner\u2019s debt] once and for all; and the life that He lives,
        He lives to [glorify] God [in unbroken fellowship with Him]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Even so, consider yourselves to be dead to sin [and your relationship
        to it broken], but alive to God [in unbroken fellowship with Him] in Christ
        Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore do not let sin reign in your mortal body so that you obey
        its lusts and passions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Do not go on offering members of your body to sin as instruments
        of wickedness. But offer yourselves to God [in a decisive act] as those alive
        [raised] from the dead [to a new life], and your members [all of your abilities\u2014sanctified,
        set apart] as instruments of righteousness [yielded] to God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For sin will no longer be a master over you, since you are not under
        Law [as slaves], but under [unmerited] grace [as recipients of God\u2019s
        favor and mercy].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "What then [are we to conclude]? Shall we sin because we are not under
        Law, but under [God\u2019s] grace? Certainly not! "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do you not know that when you continually offer yourselves to someone
        to do his will, you are the slaves of the one whom you obey, either [slaves]
        of sin, which leads to death, or of obedience, which leads to righteousness
        (right standing with God)? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But thank God that though you were slaves of sin, you became obedient
        with all your heart to the standard of teaching in which you were instructed
        and to which you were committed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And having been set free from sin, you have become the slaves of
        righteousness [of conformity to God\u2019s will and purpose]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I am speaking in [familiar] human terms because of your natural limitations
        [your spiritual immaturity]. For just as you presented your bodily members
        as slaves to impurity and to [moral] lawlessness, leading to further lawlessness,
        so now offer your members [your abilities, your talents] as slaves to righteousness,
        leading to sanctification [that is, being set apart for God\u2019s purpose].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When you were slaves of sin, you were free in regard to righteousness
        [you had no desire to conform to God\u2019s will]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So what benefit did you get at that time from the things of which
        you are now ashamed? [None!] For the outcome of those things is death! '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But now since you have been set free from sin and have become [willing]
        slaves to God, you have your benefit, resulting in sanctification [being
        made holy and set apart for God\u2019s purpose], and the outcome [of this]
        is eternal life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For the wages of sin is death, but the free gift of God [that is,
        His remarkable, overwhelming gift of grace to believers] is eternal life
        in Christ Jesus our Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Believers United to Christ'
      title: Believers United to Christ
      number: 1
      content: '  Or do you not know, brothers and sisters (for I am speaking to
        those who know the Law), that the Law has jurisdiction [to rule] over a person
        as long as he lives? '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the married woman [as an example] is bound and remains bound
        by law to her husband while he lives; but if her husband dies, she is released
        and exempt from the law concerning her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Accordingly, she will be designated as an adulteress if she unites
        herself to another man while her husband is alive. But if her husband dies,
        she is free from the law [regarding marriage], so that she is not an adulteress
        if she marries another man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Therefore, my fellow believers, you too died to the Law through the
        [crucified] body of Christ, so that you may belong to another, to Him who
        was raised from the dead, in order that we may bear fruit for God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When we were living in the flesh [trapped by sin], the sinful passions,
        which were awakened by [that which] the Law [identifies as sin], were at
        work in our body to bear fruit for death [since the willingness to sin led
        to death and separation from God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But now we have been released from the Law and its penalty, having
        died [through Christ] to that by which we were held captive, so that we serve
        [God] in the newness of the Spirit and not in the oldness of the letter [of
        the Law].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "What shall we say then? Is the Law sin? Certainly not! On the contrary,
        if it had not been for the Law, I would not have recognized sin. For I would
        not have known [for example] about coveting [what belongs to another, and
        would have had no sense of guilt] if the Law had not [repeatedly] said, \u201CYou
        shall not covet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But sin, finding an opportunity through the commandment [to express
        itself] produced in me every kind of coveting and selfish desire. For without
        the Law sin is dead [the recognition of sin is inactive]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I was once alive without [knowledge of] the Law; but when the commandment
        came [and I understood its meaning], sin became alive and I died [since the
        Law sentenced me to death]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the very commandment which was intended to bring life, actually
        proved to bring death for me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For sin, seizing its opportunity through the commandment, beguiled
        and completely deceived me, and using it as a weapon killed me [separating
        me from God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So then, the Law is holy, and the commandment is holy and righteous
        and good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Conflict of Two Natures'
      title: The Conflict of Two Natures
      number: 13
      content: 'Did that which is good [the Law], then become death to me? Certainly
        not! But sin, in order that it might be revealed as sin, was producing death
        in me by [using] this good thing [as a weapon], so that through the commandment
        sin would become exceedingly sinful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "We know that the Law is spiritual, but I am a creature of the flesh
        [worldly, self-reliant\u2014carnal and unspiritual], sold into slavery to
        sin [and serving under its control]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For I do not understand my own actions [I am baffled and bewildered
        by them]. I do not practice what I want to do, but I am doing the very thing
        I hate [and yielding to my human nature, my worldliness\u2014my sinful capacity]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now if I habitually do what I do not want to do, [that means] I agree
        with the Law, confessing that it is good (morally excellent). '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So now [if that is the case, then] it is no longer I who do it [the
        disobedient thing which I despise], but the sin [nature] which lives in me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For I know that nothing good lives in me, that is, in my flesh [my
        human nature, my worldliness\u2014my sinful capacity]. For the willingness
        [to do good] is present in me, but the doing of good is not. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the good that I want to do, I do not do, but I practice the very
        evil that I do not want. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But if I am doing the very thing I do not want to do, I am no longer
        the one doing it [that is, it is not me that acts], but the sin [nature]
        which lives in me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So I find it to be the law [of my inner self], that evil is present
        in me, the one who wants to do good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For I joyfully delight in the law of God in my inner self [with my
        new nature], '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'but I see a different law and rule of action in the members of my
        body [in its appetites and desires], waging war against the law of my mind
        and subduing me and making me a prisoner of the law of sin which is within
        my members. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Wretched and miserable man that I am! Who will [rescue me and] set
        me free from this body of death [this corrupt, mortal existence]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Thanks be to God [for my deliverance] through Jesus Christ our Lord!
        So then, on the one hand I myself with my mind serve the law of God, but
        on the other, with my flesh [my human nature, my worldliness, my sinful capacity\u2014I
        serve] the law of sin."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Escape from Bondage'
      title: Escape from Bondage
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore there is now no condemnation [no guilty verdict, no punishment]
        for those who are in Christ Jesus [who believe in Him as personal Lord and
        Savior]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the law of the Spirit of life [which is] in Christ Jesus [the
        law of our new being] has set you free from the law of sin and of death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For what the Law could not do [that is, overcome sin and remove its
        penalty, its power] being weakened by the flesh [man\u2019s nature without
        the Holy Spirit], God did: He sent His own Son in the likeness of sinful
        man as an offering for sin. And He condemned sin in the flesh [subdued it
        and overcame it in the person of His own Son], "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'so that the [righteous and just] requirement of the Law might be
        fulfilled in us who do not live our lives in the ways of the flesh [guided
        by worldliness and our sinful nature], but [live our lives] in the ways of
        the Spirit [guided by His power]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For those who are living according to the flesh set their minds on
        the things of the flesh [which gratify the body], but those who are living
        according to the Spirit, [set their minds on] the things of the Spirit [His
        will and purpose]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now the mind of the flesh is death [both now and forever\u2014because
        it pursues sin]; but the mind of the Spirit is life and peace [the spiritual
        well-being that comes from walking with God\u2014both now and forever]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "the mind of the flesh [with its sinful pursuits] is actively hostile
        to God. It does not submit itself to God\u2019s law, since it cannot, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and those who are in the flesh [living a life that caters to sinful
        appetites and impulses] cannot please God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'However, you are not [living] in the flesh [controlled by the sinful
        nature] but in the Spirit, if in fact the Spirit of God lives in you [directing
        and guiding you]. But if anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, he does
        not belong to Him [and is not a child of God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If Christ lives in you, though your [natural] body is dead because
        of sin, your spirit is alive because of righteousness [which He provides]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And if the Spirit of Him who raised Jesus from the dead lives in
        you, He who raised Christ Jesus from the dead will also give life to your
        mortal bodies through His Spirit, who lives in you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So then, brothers and sisters, we have an obligation, but not to
        our flesh [our human nature, our worldliness, our sinful capacity], to live
        according to the [impulses of the] flesh [our nature without the Holy Spirit]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for if you are living according to the [impulses of the] flesh, you
        are going to die. But if [you are living] by the [power of the Holy] Spirit
        you are habitually putting to death the sinful deeds of the body, you will
        [really] live forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For all who are allowing themselves to be led by the Spirit of God
        are sons of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For you have not received a spirit of slavery leading again to fear
        [of God\u2019s judgment], but you have received the Spirit of adoption as
        sons [the Spirit producing sonship] by which we [joyfully] cry, \u201CAbba!
        Father!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Spirit Himself testifies and confirms together with our spirit
        [assuring us] that we [believers] are children of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And if [we are His] children, [then we are His] heirs also: heirs
        of God and fellow heirs with Christ [sharing His spiritual blessing and inheritance],
        if indeed we share in His suffering so that we may also share in His glory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For I consider [from the standpoint of faith] that the sufferings
        of the present life are not worthy to be compared with the glory that is
        about to be revealed to us and in us! '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For [even the whole] creation [all nature] waits eagerly for the
        children of God to be revealed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the creation was subjected to frustration and futility, not willingly
        [because of some intentional fault on its part], but by the will of Him who
        subjected it, in hope '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'that the creation itself will also be freed from its bondage to decay
        [and gain entrance] into the glorious freedom of the children of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For we know that the whole creation has been moaning together as
        in the pains of childbirth until now. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And not only this, but we too, who have the first fruits of the Spirit
        [a joyful indication of the blessings to come], even we groan inwardly, as
        we wait eagerly for [the sign of] our adoption as sons\u2014the redemption
        and transformation of our body [at the resurrection]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For in this hope we were saved [by faith]. But hope [the object of]
        which is seen is not hope. For who hopes for what he already sees? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Our Victory in Christ'
      title: Our Victory in Christ
      number: 25
      content: 'But if we hope for what we do not see, we wait eagerly for it with
        patience and composure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'In the same way the Spirit [comes to us and] helps us in our weakness.
        We do not know what prayer to offer or how to offer it as we should, but
        the Spirit Himself [knows our need and at the right time] intercedes on our
        behalf with sighs and groanings too deep for words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And He who searches the hearts knows what the mind of the Spirit
        is, because the Spirit intercedes [before God] on behalf of God\u2019s people
        in accordance with God\u2019s will.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And we know [with great confidence] that God [who is deeply concerned
        about us] causes all things to work together [as a plan] for good for those
        who love God, to those who are called according to His plan and purpose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For those whom He foreknew [and loved and chose beforehand], He also
        predestined to be conformed to the image of His Son [and ultimately share
        in His complete sanctification], so that He would be the firstborn [the most
        beloved and honored] among many believers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And those whom He predestined, He also called; and those whom He
        called, He also justified [declared free of the guilt of sin]; and those
        whom He justified, He also glorified [raising them to a heavenly dignity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'What then shall we say to all these things? If God is for us, who
        can be [successful] against us? '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He who did not spare [even] His own Son, but gave Him up for us all,
        how will He not also, along with Him, graciously give us all things? '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Who will bring any charge against God\u2019s elect (His chosen ones)?
        It is God who justifies us [declaring us blameless and putting us in a right
        relationship with Himself]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Who is the one who condemns us? Christ Jesus is the One who died
        [to pay our penalty], and more than that, who was raised [from the dead],
        and who is at the right hand of God interceding [with the Father] for us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Who shall ever separate us from the love of Christ? Will tribulation,
        or distress, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or danger, or sword? '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Just as it is written and forever remains written,\u201CFor Your
        sake we are put to death all day long;We are regarded as sheep for the slaughter.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Yet in all these things we are more than conquerors and gain an overwhelming
        victory through Him who loved us [so much that He died for us]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "For I am convinced [and continue to be convinced\u2014beyond any
        doubt] that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor
        things present and threatening, nor things to come, nor powers, "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: nor height, nor depth, nor any other created thing, will be able to
        separate us from the [unlimited] love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our
        Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Concern for Israel'
      title: Concern for Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  I am telling the truth in Christ, I am not lying, my conscience
        testifies with me [enlightened and prompted] by the Holy Spirit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that I have great sorrow and unceasing anguish in my heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For [if it were possible] I would wish that I myself were accursed,
        [separated, banished] from Christ for the sake [of the salvation] of my brothers,
        my natural kinsmen, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'who are Israelites, to whom belongs the adoption as sons, the glory
        (Shekinah), the [special] covenants [with Abraham, Moses, and David], the
        giving of the Law, the [system of temple] worship, and the [original] promises. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'To them belong the patriarchs, and from them, according to His natural
        descent, came the Christ (the Messiah, the Anointed), He who is exalted and
        supreme over all, God blessed forever. Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "However, it is not as though God\u2019s word has failed [coming to
        nothing]. For not all who are descended from Israel (Jacob) are [the true]
        Israel; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and they are not all the children of Abraham because they are his
        descendants [by blood], but [the promise was]: \u201CYour descendants will
        be named through Isaac\u201D [though Abraham had other sons]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "That is, it is not the children of the body [Abraham\u2019s natural
        descendants] who are God\u2019s children, but it is the children of the promise
        who are counted as [Abraham\u2019s true] descendants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For this is what the promise said: \u201CAbout this time [next year]
        I will come, and Sarah shall have a son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And not only that, but this too: Rebekah conceived twin sons by one
        man [under the same circumstances], by our father Isaac; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "and though the twins were not yet born and had not done anything
        either good or bad, so that God\u2019s purpose [His choice, His election]
        would stand, not because of works [done by either child], but because of
        [the plan of] Him who calls them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "it was said to her, \u201CThe  older (Esau) will serve the  younger
        (Jacob).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As it is written and forever remains written, \u201CJacob I loved
        (chose, protected, blessed), but  Esau I hated (held in disregard compared
        to Jacob).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'What shall we say then? Is there injustice with God? Certainly not! '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For He says to Moses, \u201CI will have mercy on whomever I have
        mercy, and I will have compassion on whomever I have compassion.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So then God\u2019s choice is not dependent on human will, nor on
        human effort [the totality of human striving], but on God who shows mercy
        [to whomever He chooses\u2014it is His sovereign gift]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For the Scripture says to Pharaoh, \u201CI raised you up for this
        very purpose, to display My power in [dealing with] you, and so that My name
        would be proclaimed in all the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So then, He has mercy on whom He wills (chooses), and He hardens
        [the heart of] whom He wills.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You will say to me then, \u201CWhy does He still blame me [for sinning]?
        For who [including myself] has [ever] resisted His will and purpose?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "On the contrary, who are you, O man, who answers [arrogantly] back
        to God and dares to defy Him? Will the thing which is formed say to him who
        formed it, \u201CWhy have you made me like this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Does the potter not have the right over the clay, to make from the
        same lump [of clay] one object for honorable use [something beautiful or
        distinctive] and another for common use [something ordinary or menial]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'What if God, although willing to show His [terrible] wrath and to
        make His power known, has tolerated with great patience the objects of His
        wrath [which are] prepared for destruction? '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And what if He has done so to make known the riches of His glory
        to the objects of His mercy, which He has prepared beforehand for glory, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'including us, whom He also called, not only from among the Jews,
        but also from among the Gentiles? '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Just as He says in [the writings of the prophet] Hosea:\u201CI will
        call those who were not My people, \u2018My people,\u2019And [I will call]
        her who was not beloved, \u2018beloved.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAnd it shall be that in the place where it was said to them,
        \u2018you are not My people,\u2019There they shall be called sons of the
        living God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Isaiah calls out concerning Israel: \u201CThough the number of
        the sons of Israel be like the sand of the sea, it is only the remnant [a
        small believing minority] that will be saved [from God\u2019s judgment]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "For the Lord will execute His word upon the earth [He will conclude
        His dealings with mankind] completely and without delay.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "It is as Isaiah foretold,\u201CIf the Lord of Hosts had not left
        us seed [future generations from which a believing remnant of Israelites
        came],We would have become like Sodom, and would have resembled Gomorrah
        [totally rejected and destroyed]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'What shall we say then? That Gentiles, who did not pursue righteousness
        [who did not seek salvation and a right relationship with God, nevertheless]
        obtained righteousness, that is, the righteousness which is produced by faith; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'whereas Israel, [though always] pursuing the law of righteousness,
        did not succeed in fulfilling the law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And why not? Because it was not by faith [that they pursued it],
        but as though it were by works [relying on the merit of their works instead
        of their faith]. They stumbled over the stumbling Stone [Jesus Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "As it is written and forever remains written,\u201CBehold I am laying
        in Zion a Stone of stumbling and a Rock of offense;And he who believes in
        Him [whoever adheres to, trusts in, and relies on Him] will not be disappointed
        [in his expectations].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Word of Faith Brings Salvation'
      title: The Word of Faith Brings Salvation
      number: 1
      content: "  Brothers and sisters, my heart\u2019s desire and my prayer to God
        for Israel is for their salvation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For I testify about them that they have a certain enthusiasm for
        God, but not in accordance with [correct and vital] knowledge [about Him
        and His purposes]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For not knowing about God\u2019s righteousness [which is based on
        faith], and seeking to establish their own [righteousness based on works],
        they did not submit to God\u2019s righteousness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For Christ is the end of the law [it leads to Him and its purpose
        is fulfilled in Him], for [granting] righteousness to everyone who believes
        [in Him as Savior].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For Moses writes that the man who practices the righteousness which
        is based on law [with all its intricate demands] shall live by it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the righteousness based on faith [which produces a right relationship
        with Him] says the following: \u201CDo not say in your heart, \u2018Who will
        ascend into Heaven?\u2019 that is, to bring Christ down; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "or, \u2018Who will descend into the abyss?\u2019 that is, to bring
        Christ up from the dead [as if we had to be saved by our own efforts, doing
        the impossible].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But what does it say? \u201CThe word is near you, in your mouth and
        in your heart\u201D\u2014that is, the word [the message, the basis] of faith
        which we preach\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'because if you acknowledge and confess with your mouth that Jesus
        is Lord [recognizing His power, authority, and majesty as God], and believe
        in your heart that God raised Him from the dead, you will be saved. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For with the heart a person believes [in Christ as Savior] resulting
        in his justification [that is, being made righteous\u2014being freed of the
        guilt of sin and made acceptable to God]; and with the mouth he acknowledges
        and confesses [his faith openly], resulting in and confirming [his] salvation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the Scripture says, \u201CWhoever believes in Him [whoever adheres
        to, trusts in, and relies on Him] will not be disappointed [in his expectations].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For there is no distinction between Jew and Gentile; for the same
        Lord is Lord over all [of us], and [He is] abounding in riches (blessings)
        for all who call on Him [in faith and prayer]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For \u201Cwhoever calls on the name of the Lord [in prayer] will
        be saved.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But how will people call on Him in whom they have not believed? And
        how will they believe in Him of whom they have not heard? And how will they
        hear without a preacher (messenger)? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And how will they preach unless they are commissioned and sent [for
        that purpose]? Just as it is written and forever remains written, \u201CHow
        beautiful are the feet of those who bring good news of good things!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But they did not all pay attention to the good news [of salvation];
        for Isaiah says, \u201CLord, who has believed our report?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So faith comes from hearing [what is told], and what is heard comes
        by the [preaching of the] message concerning Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But I say, did they not hear? Indeed they have;\u201CTheir voice
        [that of creation bearing God\u2019s message] has gone out to all the earth,And
        their words to the [farthest] ends of the world.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But I say, did Israel fail to understand [that the gospel was to
        go also to the Gentiles]? First Moses says,\u201CI will make you jealous
        of those who are not a nation (Gentiles);With a nation that lacks understanding
        I will make you angry.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Isaiah is very bold and says,\u201CI have been found by those
        who did not seek Me;I have shown Myself to those who did not [consciously]
        ask for Me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But of Israel he says, \u201CAll day long I have stretched out My
        hands [in compassion] to a disobedient and obstinate people.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Is Not Cast Away'
      title: Israel Is Not Cast Away
      number: 1
      content: '  I say then, has God rejected and disowned His people? Certainly
        not! For I too am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham, of the tribe of
        Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'God has not rejected His [chosen] people whom He foreknew. Or do
        you not know what the Scripture says of Elijah, how he pleads with God against
        Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLord, they have killed Your prophets, they have torn down Your
        altars, and I alone am left [of the prophets], and they are seeking my life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But what is God\u2019s response to him? \u201CI have kept for Myself
        seven thousand men who have not bowed the knee to Baal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So too then, at the present time there has come to be a remnant [a
        small believing minority] according to God\u2019s gracious choice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But if it is by grace [God\u2019s unmerited favor], it is no longer
        on the basis of works, otherwise grace is no longer grace [it would not be
        a gift but a reward for works].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "What then? Israel failed to obtain what it was seeking [that is,
        God\u2019s favor by obedience to the Law], but the elect [those chosen few]
        obtained it, while the rest of them became hardened and callously indifferent; "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "just as it is written [in Scripture],\u201CGod gave them a spirit
        of stupor,Eyes that do not see and ears that do not hear,[a spiritual apathy
        that has continued] to this very day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And David says,\u201CLet their table (abundance) become a snare and
        a trap,A stumbling block and a retribution to them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Let their eyes be darkened so that they do not see,And make their
        backs bend [under their burden] forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So I say, have they stumbled so as to fall [to spiritual ruin]? Certainly
        not! But by their transgression [their rejection of the Messiah] salvation
        has come to the Gentiles, to make Israel jealous [when they realize what
        they have forfeited]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now if Israel\u2019s transgression means riches for the world [at
        large] and their failure means riches for the Gentiles, how much more will
        their fulfillment and reinstatement be! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But now I am speaking to you who are Gentiles. Inasmuch then as I
        am an apostle to the Gentiles, I magnify my ministry, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'in the hope of somehow making my fellow countrymen jealous [by stirring
        them up so that they will seek the truth] and perhaps save some of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For if their [present] rejection [of salvation] is for the reconciliation
        of the world [to God], what will their acceptance [of salvation] be but [nothing
        less than] life from the dead? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If the first portion [of dough offered as the first fruits] is holy,
        so is the whole batch; and if the root (Abraham, the patriarchs) is holy,
        so are the branches (the Israelites).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But if some of the branches were broken off, and you [Gentiles],
        being like a wild olive shoot, were grafted in among them to share with them
        the rich root of the olive tree, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'do not boast over the [broken] branches and exalt yourself at their
        expense. If you do boast and feel superior, remember that it is not you who
        supports the root, but the root that supports you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You will say then, \u201CBranches were broken off so that I might
        be grafted in.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "That is true. They were broken off because of their unbelief, but
        you stand by your faith [as believers understanding the truth of Christ\u2019s
        deity]. Do not be conceited, but [rather stand in great awe of God and] fear
        [Him]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'for if God did not spare the natural branches [because of unbelief],
        He will not spare you either. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then appreciate the gracious kindness and the severity of God: to
        those who fell [into spiritual ruin], severity, but to you, God\u2019s gracious
        kindness\u2014if you continue in His kindness [by faith and obedience to
        Him]; otherwise you too will be cut off. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And even they [the unbelieving Jews], if they do not continue in
        their unbelief, will be grafted in; for God has the power to graft them in
        again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For if you were cut off from what is by nature a wild olive tree,
        and against nature were grafted into a cultivated olive tree, how much easier
        will it be to graft these who are the natural branches back into [the original
        parent stock of] their own olive tree?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I do not want you, believers, to be unaware of this mystery [God\u2019s
        previously hidden plan]\u2014so that you will not be wise in your own opinion\u2014that
        a partial hardening has [temporarily] happened to Israel [to last] until
        the full number of the Gentiles has come in; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and so [at that time] all Israel [that is, all Jews who have a personal
        faith in Jesus as Messiah] will be saved; just as it is written [in Scripture],\u201CThe
        Deliverer (Messiah) will come from Zion,He will remove ungodliness from Jacob.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CThis is My covenant with them,When I take away their sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "From the standpoint of the gospel, the Jews [at present] are enemies
        [of God] for your sake [which is for your benefit], but from the standpoint
        of God\u2019s choice [of the Jews as His people], they are still loved by
        Him for the sake of the fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For the gifts and the calling of God are irrevocable [for He does
        not withdraw what He has given, nor does He change His mind about those to
        whom He gives His grace or to whom He sends His call]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Just as you once were disobedient and failed to listen to God, but
        have now obtained mercy because of their disobedience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'so they too have now become disobedient so that they too may one
        day receive mercy because of the mercy shown to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For God has imprisoned all in disobedience so that He may show mercy
        to all [Jew and Gentile alike].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Oh, the depth of the riches and wisdom and knowledge of God! How
        unsearchable are His judgments and decisions and how unfathomable and untraceable
        are His ways! '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For who has known the mind of the Lord, or who has been His counselor? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Or who has first given to Him that it would be paid back to him? '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: For from Him [all things originate] and through Him [all things live
        and exist] and to Him are all things [directed]. To Him be glory and honor
        forever! Amen.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Dedicated Service'
      title: Dedicated Service
      number: 1
      content: '    Therefore I urge you, brothers and sisters, by the mercies of
        God, to present your bodies [dedicating all of yourselves, set apart] as
        a living sacrifice, holy and well-pleasing to God, which is your rational
        (logical, intelligent) act of worship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And do not be conformed to this world [any longer with its superficial
        values and customs], but be transformed and progressively changed [as you
        mature spiritually] by the renewing of your mind [focusing on godly values
        and ethical attitudes], so that you may prove [for yourselves] what the will
        of God is, that which is good and acceptable and perfect [in His plan and
        purpose for you].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For by the grace [of God] given to me I say to everyone of you not
        to think more highly of himself [and of his importance and ability] than
        he ought to think; but to think so as to have sound judgment, as God has
        apportioned to each a degree of faith [and a purpose designed for service]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For just as in one [physical] body we have many parts, and these
        parts do not all have the same function or special use, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'so we, who are many, are [nevertheless just] one body in Christ,
        and individually [we are] parts one of another [mutually dependent on each
        other]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Since we have gifts that differ according to the grace given to us,
        each of us is to use them accordingly: if [someone has the gift of] prophecy,
        [let him speak a new message from God to His people] in proportion to the
        faith possessed;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'if service, in the act of serving; or he who teaches, in the act
        of teaching; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'or he who encourages, in the act of encouragement; he who gives,
        with generosity; he who leads, with diligence; he who shows mercy [in caring
        for others], with cheerfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Love is to be sincere and active [the real thing\u2014without guile
        and hypocrisy]. Hate what is evil [detest all ungodliness, do not tolerate
        wickedness]; hold on tightly to what is good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Be devoted to one another with [authentic] brotherly affection [as
        members of one family], give preference to one another in honor; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'never lagging behind in diligence; aglow in the Spirit, enthusiastically
        serving the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'constantly rejoicing in hope [because of our confidence in Christ],
        steadfast and patient in distress, devoted to prayer [continually seeking
        wisdom, guidance, and strength], '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "contributing to the needs of God\u2019s people, pursuing [the practice
        of] hospitality.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Bless those who persecute you [who cause you harm or hardship]; bless
        and do not curse [them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Rejoice with those who rejoice [sharing others\u2019 joy], and weep
        with those who weep [sharing others\u2019 grief]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Live in harmony with one another; do not be haughty [conceited, self-important,
        exclusive], but associate with humble people [those with a realistic self-view].
        Do not overestimate yourself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Never repay anyone evil for evil. Take thought for what is right
        and gracious and proper in the sight of everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'If possible, as far as it depends on you, live at peace with everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Beloved, never avenge yourselves, but leave the way open for God\u2019s
        wrath [and His judicial righteousness]; for it is written [in Scripture],
        \u201CVengeance is Mine, I will repay,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBut if your enemy is hungry, feed him; if he is thirsty, give
        him a drink; for by doing this you will heap  burning coals on his head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Do not be overcome and conquered by evil, but overcome evil with good.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Be Subject to Government'
      title: Be Subject to Government
      number: 1
      content: '  Let every person be subject to the governing authorities. For there
        is no authority except from God [granted by His permission and sanction],
        and those which exist have been put in place by God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Therefore whoever resists [governmental] authority resists the ordinance
        of God. And those who have resisted it will bring judgment (civil penalty)
        on themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For [civil] authorities are not a source of fear for [people of]
        good behavior, but for [those who do] evil. Do you want to be unafraid of
        authority? Do what is good and you will receive approval and commendation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For he is God\u2019s servant to you for good. But if you do wrong,
        [you should] be afraid; for he does not carry the [executioner\u2019s] sword
        for nothing. He is God\u2019s servant, an avenger who brings punishment on
        the wrongdoer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore one must be subject [to civil authorities], not only to
        escape the punishment [that comes with wrongdoing], but also as a matter
        of principle [knowing what is right before God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For this same reason you pay taxes, for civil authorities are God\u2019s
        servants, devoting themselves to governance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Pay to all what is due: tax to whom tax is due, customs to whom customs,
        respect to whom respect, honor to whom honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  Owe nothing to anyone except to love and seek the best for one
        another; for he who [unselfishly] loves his neighbor has fulfilled the [essence
        of the] law [relating to one\u2019s fellowman]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The commandments, \u201CYou shall not commit adultery, you shall
        not murder, you shall not steal, you shall not covet,\u201D and any other
        commandment are summed up in this statement: \u201CYou shall love your neighbor
        as yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Love does no wrong to a neighbor [it never hurts anyone]. Therefore
        [unselfish] love is the fulfillment of the Law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Do this, knowing that this is a critical time. It is already the
        hour for you to awaken from your sleep [of spiritual complacency]; for our
        salvation is nearer to us now than when we first believed [in Christ]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The night [this present evil age] is almost gone and the day [of
        Christ\u2019s return] is almost here. So let us fling away the works of darkness
        and put on the [full] armor of light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Let us conduct ourselves properly and honorably as in the [light
        of] day, not in carousing and drunkenness, not in sexual promiscuity and
        irresponsibility, not in quarreling and jealousy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But clothe yourselves with the Lord Jesus Christ, and make no provision
        for [nor even think about gratifying] the flesh in regard to its improper
        desires.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Principles of Conscience'
      title: Principles of Conscience
      number: 1
      content: '  As for the one whose faith is weak, accept him [into your fellowship],
        but not for [the purpose of] quarreling over his opinions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "One man\u2019s faith permits him to eat everything, while the weak
        believer eats only vegetables [to avoid eating ritually unclean meat or something
        previously considered unclean]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The one who eats [everything] is not to look down on the one who
        does not eat, and the one who does not eat must not criticize or pass judgment
        on the one who eats [everything], for God has accepted him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who are you to judge the servant of another? Before his own master
        he stands [approved] or falls [out of favor]. And he [who serves the Master\u2014the
        Lord] will stand, for the Lord is able to make him stand.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'One person regards one day as better [or more important] than another,
        while another regards every day [the same as any other]. Let everyone be
        fully convinced (assured, satisfied) in his own mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He who observes the day, observes it for the Lord. He who eats, eats
        for the Lord, since he gives thanks to God; while he who abstains, abstains
        for the Lord and gives thanks to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'None of us lives for himself [for his own benefit, but for the Lord],
        and none of us dies for himself [but for the Lord]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If we live, we live for the Lord, and if we die, we die for the Lord.
        So then, whether we live or die, we are the Lord\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For Christ died and lived again for this reason, that He might be
        Lord of both the dead and the living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But you, why do you criticize your brother? Or you again, why do
        you look down on your [believing] brother or regard him with contempt? For
        we will all stand before the judgment seat of God [who alone is judge]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For it is written [in Scripture],\u201CAs I live, says the Lord,
        every knee shall bow to Me,And every tongue shall give praise to God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So then, each of us will give an account of himself to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then let us not criticize one another anymore, but rather determine
        this\u2014not to put an obstacle or a stumbling block or a source of temptation
        in another believer\u2019s way. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I know and am convinced [as one] in the Lord Jesus that nothing is
        unclean [ritually defiled, and unholy] in itself; but [nonetheless] it is
        unclean to anyone who thinks it is unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If your brother is being hurt or offended because of food [that you
        insist on eating], you are no longer walking in love [toward him]. Do not
        let what you eat destroy and spiritually harm one for whom Christ died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore do not let what is a good thing for you [because of your
        freedom to choose] be spoken of as evil [by someone else]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for the kingdom of God is not a matter of eating and drinking [what
        one likes], but of righteousness and peace and joy in the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For the one who serves Christ in this way [recognizing that food
        choice is secondary] is acceptable to God and is approved by men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So then, let us pursue [with enthusiasm] the things which make for
        peace and the building up of one another [things which lead to spiritual
        growth]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Do not, for the sake of food, tear down the work of God. All things
        indeed are [ceremonially] clean, but they are wrong for the person who eats
        and offends [another\u2019s conscience in the process]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'It is good [to do the right thing and] not eat meat or drink wine,
        or do anything that offends your brother and weakens him spiritually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The faith which you have [that gives you freedom of choice], have
        as your own conviction before God [just keep it between yourself and God,
        seeking His will]. Happy is he who has no reason to condemn himself for what
        he approves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: But he who is uncertain [about eating a particular thing] is condemned
        if he eats, because he is not acting from faith. Whatever is not from faith
        is sin [whatever is done with doubt is sinful].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Self-denial on Behalf of Others'
      title: Self-denial on Behalf of Others
      number: 1
      content: '  Now we who are strong [in our convictions and faith] ought to [patiently]
        put up with the weaknesses of those who are not strong, and not just please
        ourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let each one of us [make it a practice to] please his neighbor for
        his good, to build him up spiritually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For even Christ did not please Himself; but as it is written [in
        Scripture], \u201CThe reproaches of those who reproached You (the Father)
        fell on Me (the Son).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For whatever was written in earlier times was written for our instruction,
        so that through endurance and the encouragement of the Scriptures we might
        have hope and overflow with confidence in His promises. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now may the God who gives endurance and who supplies encouragement
        grant that you be of the same mind with one another according to Christ Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'so that with one accord you may with one voice glorify and praise
        and honor the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore, [continue to] accept and welcome one another, just as
        Christ has accepted and welcomed us to the glory of [our great] God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For I tell you that Christ has become a servant and a minister to
        the circumcision (Jews) on behalf of God\u2019s truth, to confirm and verify
        the promises made to the fathers, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and for the Gentiles to glorify God for His mercy [to them, since
        God had no covenant with them]. As it is written and forever remains written,\u201CTherefore
        I praise You among the Gentiles,And sing praises to Your name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Again it says,\u201CRejoice  and  celebrate, O Gentiles, along with
        His people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And again,\u201CPraise the Lord all you Gentiles,And let all the
        peoples praise Him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Again Isaiah says,\u201CThere shall be a root of  Jesse,He who arises
        to rule [as King] over the Gentiles,In Him shall the Gentiles hope.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'May the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing
        [through the experience of your faith] that by the power of the Holy Spirit
        you will abound in hope and overflow with confidence in His promises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Personally I am convinced about you, my brothers and sisters, that
        you yourselves are full of goodness, amply filled with all [spiritual] knowledge,
        and competent to admonish and counsel and instruct one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Still, on some points I have written to you very boldly and without
        reservation to remind you [about them] again, because of the grace that was
        given to me from God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'to be a minister of Christ Jesus to the Gentiles. I minister as a
        priest the gospel of God, in order that my offering of the Gentiles may become
        acceptable [to Him], sanctified [made holy and set apart for His purpose]
        by the Holy Spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In Christ Jesus, then, I have found [legitimate] reason for boasting
        in things related [to my service] to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For I will not [even] presume to speak of anything except what Christ
        has done through me [as an instrument in His hands], resulting in the obedience
        of the Gentiles [to the gospel], by word and deed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'with the power of signs and wonders, [and all of it] in the power
        of the Spirit. So [starting] from Jerusalem and as far away as Illyricum,
        I have fully preached the gospel [faithfully preaching the good news] of
        Christ [where it had not before been preached]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Accordingly I set a goal to preach the gospel, not where Christ\u2019s
        name was already known, so that I would not build on another man\u2019s foundation; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "but [instead I would act on this goal] as it is written [in Scripture],\u201CThey
        who had no news of Him shall see,And they who have not heard [of Him] shall
        understand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "This [goal\u2014my commitment to this principle] is the reason why
        I have often been prevented from coming to you [in Rome]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But now, with no further place for work in these regions, and since
        I have longed for many years to come to you\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "whenever I go [on my trip] to Spain\u2014I hope to see you as I pass
        through [Rome], and to be helped on my journey there by you, after I have
        first enjoyed your company for a little while. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But for now, I am going to Jerusalem to serve the saints (Jewish
        believers). '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For [Gentile believers in] Macedonia and Achaia have been pleased
        to make a contribution for the poor among the saints (Jewish believers) in
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They were pleased to do it, and they are indebted to them. For if
        the Gentiles have come to share in their spiritual things, then they are
        indebted to serve them also in [tangible] material things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore, when I have finished this [mission] and have safely given
        to them what has been raised, I will go on by way of you to Spain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I know that when I do come to you, I will come in the abundant blessing
        of Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I urge you, believers, by our Lord Jesus Christ and by the love of
        the Spirit, to join together with me in your prayers to God in my behalf, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '[and pray] that I may be rescued from the unbelievers in Judea, and
        that my service for Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints (Jewish believers)
        there;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "so that by God\u2019s will I may come to you with joy and find rest
        in your company. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: May the God of peace be with you all! Amen.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greetings and Love Expressed'
      title: Greetings and Love Expressed
      number: 1
      content: '  Now I introduce and commend to you our sister Phoebe, a deaconess
        (servant) of the church at Cenchrea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "that you may receive her in the Lord [with love and hospitality],
        as God\u2019s people ought to receive one another. And that you may help
        her in whatever matter she may require assistance from you, for she has been
        a helper of many, including myself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Greet Prisca and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'who risked their own necks [endangering their very lives] for my
        life. To them not only do I give thanks, but also all the churches of the
        Gentiles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Also greet the church that meets in their house. Greet my beloved
        Epaenetus, who is the first convert to Christ from [the west coast province
        of] Asia [Minor]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Greet Mary, who has worked so hard for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Greet Andronicus and Junias, my kinsmen and [once] my fellow prisoners,
        who are held in high esteem in the estimation of the apostles, and who were
        [believers] in Christ before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Greet Ampliatus, my beloved in the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Greet Urbanus, our fellow worker in Christ, and my beloved Stachys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Greet Apelles, the one tested and approved in Christ. Greet those
        who belong to the household of Aristobulus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Greet my kinsman Herodion. Greet those of the household of Narcissus,
        who are in the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Greet those workers in the Lord, Tryphaena and Tryphosa. Greet my
        beloved Persis, who has worked hard in the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Greet Rufus, an eminent and choice man in the Lord, also his mother
        [who has been] a mother to me as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brothers
        who are with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Greet Philologus and Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas, and
        all God\u2019s people who are with them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Greet one another with a holy kiss. All the churches of Christ greet
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I urge you, brothers and sisters, to keep your eyes on those who
        cause dissensions and create obstacles or introduce temptations [for others]
        to commit sin, [acting in ways] contrary to the doctrine which you have learned.
        Turn away from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For such people do not serve our Lord Christ, but their own appetites
        and base desires. By smooth and flattering speech they deceive the hearts
        of the unsuspecting [the innocent and the naive]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the report of your obedience has reached everyone, so that I
        rejoice over you, but I want you to be wise in what is good and innocent
        in what is evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The God of peace will soon crush Satan under your feet.  The [wonderful]
        grace of our Lord Jesus be with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Timothy, my fellow worker, sends his greetings to you, as do Lucius,
        Jason and Sosipater, my kinsmen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I, Tertius, the writer (scribe) of this letter, greet you in the
        Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Gaius, who is host to me and to the whole church here, greets you.
        Erastus, the city treasurer, and our brother Quartus, greet you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '[The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now to Him who is able to establish and strengthen you [in the faith]
        according to my gospel and the preaching of Jesus Christ, according to the
        revelation of the mystery [of the plan of salvation] which has been kept
        secret for long ages past, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'but now has been disclosed and through the prophetic Scriptures has
        been made known to all the nations, according to the commandment of the eternal
        God, leading them to obedience to the faith, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: to the only wise God, through Jesus Christ, be the glory forevermore!
        Amen.
      comments: []
